!TP_LOCALLAB_SATCIE_TOOLTIP;Modifies the image saturation whenever the gamma/slope ratio is different from 2.4/12.92. It aims to compensate for the desaturation caused by significant luminance variations.\nValues ​​between 0.2 and 1.0 are often sufficient.
